excerpt: Tours of a rum distillery, along with cocktail workshops & an open-air bar serving drinks & tapas.
detail_description: If you're looking to dive into the vibrant spirit of Phuket, The Distillery Phuket - Home of Chalong Bay is a must-visit destination. This award-winning rum distillery offers an immersive experience where you can witness the fascinating process of rum production, from sugarcane pressing to fermentation and distillation. Made entirely from 100% natural Thai sugarcane grown without harmful chemicals, Chalong Bay's artisan rum stands out for its purity and quality.
name: The Distillery Phuket - Home of Chalong Bay
address: 14, 2 Soi Palai, Chalong, Amphur Muang, Phuket 83130, Thailand

excerpt: The 45m-tall marble Buddha statue on a mountaintop offers panoramic views, a cafe & gift shop.
detail_description: The Big Buddha, officially known as "Phraphutthamingmongkhol-akenagakhiri Buddha," stands majestically at 45 meters tall atop Nakerd Mountain in Phuket. This stunning white marble statue is not only a significant religious site but also offers breathtaking panoramic views of the island, including Phuket Town and Chalong Bay. The journey to this iconic landmark is made easy with well-paved roads, despite some winding curves.
name: The Big Buddha, Phuket
address: Karon, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83100, Thailand

excerpt: Large temple complex from the early 19th century, with Buddha paintings, golden statues & gardens.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Phuket, Chaithararam Temple, also known as Wat Chalong, is a stunning temple complex that dates back to the early 19th century. This sacred site is adorned with intricate Buddha paintings and shimmering golden statues, surrounded by beautifully landscaped gardens that invite tranquility. The temple holds significant historical importance for the local community, particularly due to its association with Luangpho Chaem—a revered monk known for his mastery in meditation and traditional medicine.
name: Wat Chalong
address: 70 หมู่ที่ 6 Chao Fah Tawan Tok Rd, Chalong, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Spacious animal park with many colorful species of birds in a lush setting with regular bird shows.
detail_description: Nestled in a lush setting, Phuket Bird Park is a spacious animal park showcasing a wide variety of colorful bird species. Visitors can enjoy regular bird shows and close-up encounters with the local avian population. Covering 12 acres of gardens and habitats, the park is home to over 100 different bird variations, offering an immersive experience in the world of birds.
name: Phuket Bird Park
address: 6/2 Chao Fah Tawan Tok Rd, Wichit, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Lively Phuket Old Town is known for brightly painted, century-old Sino-Portuguese townhouses, with a well-preserved row along Soi Rommanee. Main street Thalang Road has stores selling artisanal ice cream and batik fabrics and a Sunday market for souvenirs and street food like fried banana. The Thai Hua Museum features exhibits on Chinese immigrant culture, and Jui Tui Shrine displays colorful statues of Chinese gods.
detail_description: Old Phuket Town is a vibrant area known for its well-preserved Sino-Portuguese townhouses, artisanal shops, and colorful markets. Visitors can explore the Thai Hua Museum and Jui Tui Shrine to learn about Chinese immigrant culture and see colorful statues of Chinese gods.
name: Old Phuket Town
address: Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Chalong is an urban-commercial bay area dominated by the hilltop Big Buddha statue. Colorful temple complex Wat Chalong also offers sweeping views over the Andaman Sea. Busy pubs and seafood restaurants surround Ao Chalong pier, where day trippers depart on sailing and diving excursions. Visitors come to see the Botanic Garden’s orchids and butterflies, while Phuket Bird Park is home to parrots and ostriches.
detail_description: Chalong is a bustling bay area known for its urban-commercial vibe and the iconic Big Buddha statue perched on a hilltop. The vibrant Wat Chalong temple complex offers stunning panoramic views of the Andaman Sea, while Ao Chalong pier serves as a hub for sailing and diving excursions. Nature enthusiasts can explore the Botanic Garden's orchids and butterflies, or visit Phuket Bird Park to see parrots and ostriches.
name: Chalong
address: Mueang Phuket District, Phuket, Thailand

excerpt: Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand’s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. Set in a 1930s manor, the Thai Hua Museum has exhibits on Phuket’s culture and history.
detail_description: Phuket, the vibrant capital of Thailand's Phuket Province, is a treasure trove of culture and history. Strolling through Old Town, you'll be captivated by the colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese architecture that line Thalang Road. A visit to Baan Chinpracha mansion reveals its stunning Italian floor tiles and antique furnishings, while the Thai Hua Museum offers fascinating insights into local heritage within a charming 1930s manor.
name: Phuket
address: Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Kid-friendly aquarium with fish & coral reef displays, plus an underwater tunnel & a touch pool.
detail_description: Nestled in Cape Panwa, the Phuket Aquarium is a delightful destination for families and marine enthusiasts alike. While it may not be vast, its charm lies in its captivating displays of local marine life. Visitors can marvel at impressive tanks housing fascinating creatures such as leopard sharks, moray eels, giant groupers, and even piranhas from the Amazon.
name: Phuket Aquarium
address: 51 หมู่ที่ 8, ถนน ศักดิเดช, Wichit, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Well-known destination for picturesque views of the ocean, beaches & lush island surroundings.
detail_description: Karon Viewpoint is a must-visit gem in Phuket, offering breathtaking panoramas of the Andaman Sea and the stunning beaches that line the coast. Nestled just south of Kata Noi Beach, this popular spot allows visitors to gaze upon three beautiful bays: Kata Noi, Kata, and Karon. The viewpoint is particularly enchanting at dusk when the sky transforms into vibrant hues of pink and red.
name: Karon Viewpoint
address: 4233, Karon, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83100, Thailand

excerpt: Colorful 1911 Chinese shrine & the site of the annual Phuket Vegetarian Festival.
detail_description: Jui Tui Shrine, a vibrant Chinese shrine in Phuket, is known for its annual Vegetarian Festival. After undergoing renovations, the shrine now houses three large statues of different Chinese gods, with Tean Hu Huan Soy being the most prominent. The shrine's location was moved following a fire that nearly destroyed it years ago. Visitors can also see a firecracker house next to the shrine where people often throw burning firecrackers during celebrations.
name: San Chao Jui Tui
address: 283 Soi Phutorn, Talat Nuea, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Rawai is a village on the southeast coast of Thailand’s Phuket Island. Rawai Beach is known for its long-tailed boats, the Sea Gypsies Fish Market and seafood restaurants. Phuket Seashell Museum displays rare shells from Thailand and around the world. To the south, Promthep Cape has a lighthouse and views over the Andaman Sea. Offshore islands like Coral Island have white sand, palm trees and coral reefs.
detail_description: Rawai is a charming village situated on the southeast coast of Phuket Island in Thailand. The area is renowned for its picturesque Rawai Beach, where visitors can admire traditional long-tailed boats and indulge in delectable seafood at the local restaurants. Additionally, tourists can explore the Sea Gypsies Fish Market and marvel at rare shells from Thailand and around the world at the Phuket Seashell Museum.
name: Rawai
address: Mueang Phuket District, Phuket, Thailand

excerpt: Tourist attraction featuring up-close interaction with tigers in caged enclosures.
detail_description: Tiger Kingdom in Phuket offers a unique and unforgettable experience for visitors to get up close and personal with tigers in safe, caged enclosures. The attraction provides an opportunity to learn about these majestic animals, take a leisurely walk through the park, and even feed or take photos with the tigers. With premium insurance included in the ticket, visitors can also explore educational exhibits and enjoy a personal encounter with the tigers.
name: Tiger Kingdom - Phuket
address: 118/88 Moo 7, Kathu, Phuket, Thailand

detail_description: Step into a world of optical illusions and mind-bending art at the AR Trick Eye Museum Phuket. This museum features themed rooms such as the aqua zone, jungle, art masterpieces, and more, where visitors can interact with 3D paintings that create stunning optical illusions. Located in Phuket Town, this two-story building showcases about 100 painted and sculpted scenes using trompe-l'oeil techniques.
name: Trick Eye Museum Phuket
address: 199 Moo4 T.Wichit, A, Mueang Phuket District, 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Expansive rainforest adventure park featuring treetop walkways & zip lines.
detail_description: Hanuman World is a thrilling rainforest adventure park in Phuket, Thailand, offering treetop walkways and exhilarating zip lines. The 800-meter zipline ride provides an adrenaline-pumping experience as it twists through the dense canopy at high speeds. Visitors can embark on a ziplining journey across 32 platforms in the treetops, enjoying the support of friendly staff.
name: Hanuman World
address: 105 หมู่ที่ 4 ถนนเหมืองเจ้าฟ้า, Wichit, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: This beach adjacent to resorts & restaurants features swimming, diving & other activities.
detail_description: Kata Noi Beach, a hidden gem on Phuket's southwest coast, offers an idyllic escape with its stunning white sands and crystal-clear aquamarine waters. Nestled in a serene bay just south of the bustling Karon Beach, this beach is perfect for families seeking relaxation away from the party scene of Patong. The 1.5 km stretch is lined with swaying palm trees that provide shade while vendors offer refreshing drinks and local snacks right at your fingertips.
name: Kata Noi Beach
address: Karon, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83100, Thailand

detail_description: Jungle Xtrem Adventure And Zipline Park, also known as Phuket Tree Adventure, is a thrilling destination located in a rubber plantation above Wat Chalong. The 19,200-square-meter park offers various activities such as tightropes, flying fox, net walking, and different types of bridges. Safety is a top priority here with each participant being equipped with safety harnesses and other gear before embarking on the adventure.
name: Jungle Xtrem Adventure And Zipline Park
address: 54, 17, Chalong, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83130, Thailand

detail_description: Chalong Pier Meeting Point is a popular spot for those looking to enjoy the serene blue sea and stunning views. The pier stretches for about a kilometer, with free truck rides available to reach its end. It serves as the main departure point for diving boats, catering to both recreational and professional divers. From here, visitors can also catch sight of the impressive giant Buddha statue.
name: Chalong Pier Meeting Point
address: 12 Sunrise Rd, Chalong, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83100, Thailand

detail_description: The Phuket Snake Show is currently undergoing renovations and does not have ongoing shows, but visitors can still interact with the crocodiles by feeding them chicken and taking photos for a fee. The park has been impacted by COVID-19 restrictions, leading to an abandoned atmosphere. Despite this, visitors have found it to be a unique experience and are glad they took the chance to visit.
name: Phuket Snake Show
address: 1/95 moo 5, Chalong, Muang, Phuket, 83130, Thailand

excerpt: Compact zoo featuring live crocodile, elephant & monkey performances.
detail_description: Phuket Zoo is a popular destination for families looking to provide their children with exciting and educational experiences. The zoo offers a variety of activities, including the chance to interact with animals, watch circus performances featuring elephants, monkeys, and crocodiles, feed the animals, and take photos with them. The compact 12-acre zoo is home to a diverse range of wildlife such as ostriches, peacocks, tigers, crocodiles, and elephants.
name: Phuket Zoo
address: 23 Soi Pa Lai 2, Chalong, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83130, Thailand

detail_description: Hidden Forest Elephant Reserve is a sanctuary in Phuket that offers an incredible experience for visitors. The team has created a special environment where the elephants come first, ensuring they are treated with respect and care. Visitors can have a magical experience feeding the elephants and observing them as they move freely throughout the grounds. This sanctuary stands out for its ethical practices, offering a peaceful and calm atmosphere for both visitors and elephants.
name: Hidden Forest Elephant Reserve - Sanctuary in Phuket
address: 38, 1 Soi Nakok, Chalong, Phuket, 83130, Thailand
